data.text: Ozaki Yukio (尾崎 行雄 Ozaki Yukio, born December 24, 1858) is a Japanese politician of liberal signature, born in Manato, Kanagawa. Ozaki has been serving in the House of Representatives of the Japanese Diet for 42 years (1890–1932) and the current Prime Minister of Japan (1930–present). He is being revered in Japan as the "God of Constitutional Politics" and the "Father of the Japanese Constitution".
